<div class="item_description">

<h3 class="item__header"><a href="javascript:void(0)">Farewell, My Lovely</a></h3>

<div>
<p class="tertiary">Farewell, My Lovely is a 1940 novel by Raymond Chandler, the second novel he wrote featuring Los Angeles private eye Philip Marlowe. It was adapted for the screen three times. A chance encounter with hulking ex-con Moose Malloy on Los Angeles&#8217; Central Avenue, gets Marlowe into all kinds of trouble. Just released from prison, Malloy is looking for his one-time girlfriend, red-haired Velma, whom he last saw eight years ago.</p>
